Agile
in the area of ​​software development mainly in the management of software projects
approach that helps teams around the world deliver more value to customers faster and with far fewer headaches
deliver the constants with small increments and that those famous deliverables are consumable is the best approach

"The main objective of agile teams is not to deliver a final product, according to certain requirements, but to deliver value to the customer. That is, to deliver a solution that brings the best results."


Devops
is the combination of practices and tools to increase (through automation, collaboration, fast feedback, and iterative improvement) an organization's ability to deliver applications and services 
improves the Mean Time to Recovery (MTTR - average time it takes to recover from a product or system failure) when incidents and outages occur
